# Enforcement surfaces: the files whose content decides merge verdicts.
# With require_code_owner_review enabled on the Protect-Main ruleset, a
# PR touching these paths cannot merge without an approval from a
# non-author code owner -- a server-side layer the judged PR's merge
# ref cannot edit.
#
# Deliberately no `*` rule: under require_code_owner_review a global
# owner would make that owner a required approver for every PR, not
# just the enforcement surfaces. Ordinary PRs keep the plain
# one-approval rule.

